<h3 class="title2">CGIAR-shared learning resources</h3>
<p class="text" style="text-align: justify; ">This third section of the learning resources page links to an externally managed site for CGIAR system wide materials, and is searchable separately. CIP, working with various other CGIAR centers, helped to establish this site (through the ICT-KM sponsored Open Learning Resources/OLR project). Over the past 3 or 4 years it has begun to facilitate more open access to CGIAR-shared learning resources, considered as international public goods (IPG) freely and openly accessible to all.</p>
<p class="text" style="text-align: justify; ">Materials on that site (<a href="http://learning.cgiar.org/" target="_blank">http://learning.cgiar.org/</a>) represent two types of existing materials. The first is a repository of basic learning resources, including manuals and re-usable learning objects (RLOs), some from the 1970s on, which may be interchangeable, recombined, and used for different purposes. The second is a Learning Management System (LMS) or “Moodle” with a growing array of open or facilitated online courses on various specialized topics of interest to the CGIAR members and their partners.</p>